Semantic vs Non-Semantic Tags
📘 Definitions
Semantic Tags:
Tags that have their own meaning.
They clearly describe their purpose.

Examples:
nav, main, footer, header, section, article

Non-Semantic Tags:
Tags that do not describe their purpose.

Examples:
div, span, p, custom tags







-> Block vs Inline Elements
📘 Definitions
Block Elements:
Start on a new line
Take full width of the page

Examples:
h1-h6, p, div, nav, footer

Inline Elements:
Do not start on a new line
Take only required width

Examples:
span, a, img, input

✅ Code Example
