🔹 What is Class in HTML?
-> Class is used to apply the same CSS style
to multiple elements.

-> In CSS we use "." (dot) before class name.

Example:
.first_class { }


🔹 What is ID in HTML?
-> ID is used to apply CSS to a unique element.

-> In CSS we use "#" before ID name.

Example:
#second_class_id { }

📌 Code
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>CSS Class & ID</title>

  <style>
    /* Element Selector */
    h1 {
      background-color: black;
      color: whitesmoke;
    }

    /* Styling all <p> elements */
    p {
      background-color: green;
      color: whitesmoke;
      height: 200px;
      width: 400px;
